Deal with missing data

In[]:
from scipy.stats import entropy

kl_divergences = {}
data_cleaned = data.dropna()

for feature in features:
  hist_original, bin_edges = np.histogram(data[feature].dropna(), bins=50, density=True)
  hist_cleaned, _ = np.histogram(data_cleaned[feature].dropna(), bins=bin_edges, density=True)

  hist_original += 1e-10
  hist_cleaned += 1e-10

  kl_div = entropy(hist_original, hist_cleaned)
  kl_divergences[feature] = kl_div

print("KL Divergence for each feature before and after dropping NAs:")
for feature, kl_div in kl_divergences.items():
    print(f"{feature}: {kl_div:.4f}")

In[86]:
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_samples
import matplotlib.cm as cm

def silhouett_plot(sample_silhouette_values, silhouette_avg, cluster_labels):
  n_clusters = len(np.unique(cluster_labels))
  y_lower = 10
  for i in range(n_clusters):
     ith_cluster_silhouette_values = sample_silhouette_values[cluster_labels == i]
     ith_cluster_silhouette_values.sort()

     size_cluster_i = ith_cluster_silhouette_values.shape[0]
     y_upper = y_lower + size_cluster_i

     color = cm.nipy_spectral(float(i) / n_clusters)
     plt.fill_betweenx(np.arange(y_lower, y_upper),0,
        ith_cluster_silhouette_values,
        facecolor=color,
        edgecolor=color,
        alpha=0.7,
     )
     plt.text(-0.05, y_lower + 0.5 * size_cluster_i, str(i))
     y_lower = y_upper + 10
     plt.xlabel("The silhouette coefficient values")
     plt.ylabel("Cluster label")
     plt.axvline(x=silhouette_avg, color="red", linestyle="--")
  return plt.gca()

from sklearn.mixture import GaussianMixture
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV


def gmm_bic_score(estimator, X):
  return -estimator.bic(X)
param_grid = {
  "n_components": range(1, 7),
  "covariance_type": ["spherical", "tied", "diag", "full"],
}
grid_search = GridSearchCV(GaussianMixture(init_params='k-means++'), param_grid=param_grid, scoring=gmm_bic_score)
grid_search.fit(data_pca)

Meanshift

In[94]:
from sklearn.cluster import MeanShift, estimate_bandwidth
quantiles = [0.2, 0.3, 0.4, 0.5]
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,4, figsize=(16, 4))
for i,q in enumerate(quantiles):
  bandwidth = estimate_bandwidth(data_pca, quantile=q, n_samples=500)
  ms = MeanShift(bandwidth=bandwidth,bin_seeding=True)
  ms.fit(data_pca)
  sample_silhouette_values = silhouette_samples(data_pca, ms.labels_, )
  silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(data_pca, ms.labels_)
  plt.sca(axes[i])
  silhouett_plot(sample_silhouette_values=sample_silhouette_values, silhouette_avg=silhouette_avg, cluster_labels=ms.labels_)
  axes[i].set_title(f"Silhouette plot of meanshift clustering\n(n={len(np.unique(ms.labels_))}, quantile={q})")
